      "comment_id" : 140747061,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Sure it works and if you run it a couple of times it will always do what it should do.   However it is not a try with resources. This is simply a catch block. If this code snippet is run often and sometimes the Exception is thrown, then the TempFiles will not be deleted until the JVM exits and if the JVM crashes, it might not be deleted at all.   I would strongly prefer to put the Files.delete in a finally block. That way it is always executed , even if an exception is thrown."
