    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To create a safe temporary file in Java, use the <code>Files.createTempFile()</code> method from <code>java.nio.file</code> or <code>File.createTempFile()</code> from <code>java.io</code>.</p>\n<p>Both of these methods can</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Generate unique names automatically</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Use the system temp directory</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Handle race conditions</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Set appropriate permissions</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>An example using try-with-resources to ensure deletion:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>void foo() {\n    try {\n        // Create temp file that will be deleted when the JVM exits\n        Path tempFile = Files.createTempFile(&quot;prefix-&quot;, &quot;-suffix&quot;);\n        \n        // Register for deletion on JVM exit (extra safety)\n        tempFile.toFile().deleteOnExit();\n        \n        // Use the temp file\n        Files.write(tempFile, &quot;Hello World&quot;.getBytes());\n        // If you are using Log, use Log.debug()\n        System.out.println(&quot;Created temp file: &quot; + tempFile);\n        \n        // Delete explicitly when done\n        Files.delete(tempFile);\n\n    } catch (IOException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
